&lt;p&gt;The South CAMHS Getting More Help Service are looking for an enthusiastic, creative and inspiring Mental Health Practitioner to join the team. This is an opportunity to work within an experienced multidisciplinary team, providing Mental Health support to the south locality.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role will include managing a case load, offering both routine and emergency mental health assessments. Taking part in the duty rota, liaising with the local community including schools, charities and the private sector. The successful candidate will also offer evidence based interventions, either face to face, using an IT platform such as Microsoft teams or telephone consultation. Within the role you will also offer clinical supervision and support the development of junior staff.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The main office is based at the Clockhouse in Abingdon on Thames but as a team we cover localities across South Oxfordshire, including rural and remote locations, and as such access to transport for business use is essential for the role.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameKelly GarsideJob titleClincial Team ManagerEmail addresskelly.garside@oxfordhealth.nhs.ukTelephone number01865-904700Additional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you would like to discuss this post or arrange for an informal visit, then do contact Kelly Garside or Amanda Winfield on 01865-904700.&lt;/p&gt;
